nodes.bodyText:
@Gaurav-Punjabi I think the right replacement for the ternary operator from the Check description is
String b;
if (a == null || a.length() < 1) {
  b = null;
 }
else {
  b = a.substring(1);
}

or, even better:
String b;
if (a != null && a.length() >= 1) {
  b = a.substring(1);
 }
else {
  b = null;
}

Please remove all examples like ? true : false;   and use something real.

